# Sanity Studio

Docs: [content-modeling.md](../../apps/web/docs/content-modeling.md)

## Before any studio work

Read and follow the **Sanity best-practices skill** listed under `available_skills` in the session context.

## TypeGen ‚Äî run after every schema change

```bash
yarn typegen
```

Run whenever a field is added, removed, or renamed; when a type is registered or removed; or when `variant`/`size` options change on `buttonBlock`.

## ButtonBlock ‚Üí CVA pipeline

Studio `buttonBlock.ts` is the **SSoT** for button variant and size options. The web derives `ColorVariant` / `SizeVariant` from the generated `ButtonBlock` type via `components/ui/variants.ts`. After changing options, run `yarn typegen` ‚Äî mismatched CVA keys surface as TypeScript errors.

## Shared option constants

When a schema field uses a `list` of `{title, value}` options that also need a display label in the web app, add the array to `packages/release-constants/index.ts` ‚Äî not inside either app. The Studio re-exports from there; the web derives label maps with `Object.fromEntries`. See [content-modeling.md](../../apps/web/docs/content-modeling.md#shared-option-constants----packagesrelease-constants).

## Singleton ID constants

Never hardcode singleton document IDs ‚Äî use the exported constants:

```ts
import { SITE_SETTINGS_ID } from '../schemaTypes/siteSettings'
import { RELEASES_PAGE_ID } from '../schemaTypes/releasesPage'
```
